[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1011[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Putting It All Together
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1012[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1013[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Here's the full fusion pipeline assembled into a single callable function. In production, each step would be a separate task in an AWS Step Functions state machine. Here we run them sequentially for clarity.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1014[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1015[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1016[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def run_fusion_pipeline(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1017[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     fixed_modality: str = "CT",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1018[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     moving_modality: str = "MR",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1019[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     body_region: str = "brain",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1020[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1021[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1022[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Run the complete multi-modal imaging fusion pipeline.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1023[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1024[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This demonstrates the end-to-end flow using synthetic data:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1025[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     1. Create synthetic study volumes (simulating HealthImaging retrieval)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1026[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     2. Preprocess each modality
